The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Wicketkeeper-Captains in Tests
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Wicketkeeper-Captains in Tests
                      
	Mahendra Singh Dhoni on Friday became the first wicketkeeper to lead India in a Test. He is also, overall, the 25th to lead a Test side.         
	 The following is the list:           W.L. Murdoch (Aus)  J.M. Blackham (Aus)  E.A. Halliwell (SA)   M. Bisset (SA)  P.W. Sherwell (SA)  R.T. Stanyforth (Eng)  R.K. Nunes (WI)  H.B. Cameron (SA)  F.C.M. Alexander (WI)  Imtiaz Ahmed (Pak)  B.N. Jarman (Aus)  Wasim Bari (Pak)  D.L. Murray (WI)  I.D.S. Smith (NZ)  Alec Stewart (Eng)  Andy Flower (Zim)  L.K. Germon (NZ)  Rashid Latif (Pak)  Moin Khan (Pak)  Adam Gilchrist (Aus)  Khaled Mashud (Ban)  Mark Boucher (SA)  Ridley Jacobs (WI)  Tatenda Taibu (Zim)  Mahendra Singh Dhoni (Ind)      COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                      
